article.headline: New Orleans 87, Louisiana Tech 85 (OT)
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Jamie McNeilly hit a 3-pointer with 3 seconds left to give New Orleans an 87-85 overtime victory over Louisiana Tech Saturday. Bo McCalebb scored 26 points -- the 15th consecutive time he scored more than 20 points in a game -- to lead the Privateers (12-14). James Parlow added 22 and Shawn Malloy finished with 19 and nine rebounds. Paul Millsap led the Bulldogs (13-11) with 22 points and 12 rebounds. Donell Allick added 16 points, Wayne Powell had 13 and Corey Dean had 11. The game was tied at 72 at the end of regulation.
